      <div class="card-title">User Preferences</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Persistent per-project key-value store via <code>set_preference(key, value)</code>. Written to <code>.gondola_memory.json</code> and surfaced in the system prompt on every new session.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ CONTEXT ═══ -->
<section class="section" id="context">
  <div class="section-label">10 — Token Management</div>
  <h2 class="section-title"><span class="icon">📡</span>Context Engine &amp; Compression</h2>

  <div class="info-box">
    The <strong>ContextManager</strong> ensures Gondola stays within model token limits without losing critical information. It allocates a token budget per message category and compresses old content intelligently.
  </div>

  <div class="card-grid">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">Budget Allocation</div>
      <div class="card-desc">System prompt: min(4000, context÷8) tokens. Project context: min(2000, context÷10) tokens. Remaining budget is split: 50% for older messages, 50% for recent messages.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">File Content Compression</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Large files are truncated to the first 50 lines + last 30 lines. The omitted middle section is described as <em>"[N lines omitted — lines 51 to M]"</em> so the model knows what was cut.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">File List Compression</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Listings over 50 files are grouped by directory with counts. e.g., <em>"src/components/: Button, Modal, ... +12 more"</em>. Up to 20 directories shown.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">Search Result Compression</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Over 10 search matches: shows top 10 in full, plus a list of additional files that matched. Preserves the most relevant context while noting the total match count.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">Command Output Compression</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Always preserves stderr in full (usually contains errors). Truncates stdout at 20K chars. Exit code is always preserved regardless of output length.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">Truncation Awareness</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Every compression event adds a notice to <code>truncation_notices</code>. At the start of the next model call, these are injected as a system warning: <em>"⚠️ CONTEXT NOTICE: The following was truncated..."</em></div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">Sliding Window</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Always keeps the last 4 messages in full. Older messages are compressed further. If adding an old message would exceed 50% of the conversation budget, it is dropped entirely.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">GLM-Series Optimization</div>
      <div class="card-desc">System prompts are stripped of filler language to maximize signal-to-noise ratio. Context is structured to match GLM's superior performance with complex function schemas and unique attention-weighting architecture.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ SYSTEM PROMPT ═══ -->
<section class="section" id="system-prompt">
  <div class="section-label">11 — Prompt Engineering</div>
  <h2 class="section-title"><span class="icon">📝</span>System Prompt Architecture</h2>

  <div class="info-box">
    The system prompt is rebuilt on <strong>every turn</strong> via <code>build_system_prompt()</code> to keep turn counts, project context, and state fresh. It is composed of up to 10 ordered sections, each conditionally included based on session state.
  </div>

  <ol class="flow-list">
    <li>
      <div class="flow-num">1</div>
      <div class="flow-content">
        <div class="flow-step">BASE</div>
        <div class="flow-desc">Static core mandates: tool usage rules, output format, safety constraints. Never changes at runtime.</div>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <div class="flow-num">2</div>
      <div class="flow-content">
        <div class="flow-step">PERSONALITY</div>
        <div class="flow-desc">Injected from <code>.personality_config</code> if present. Loaded fresh each turn — changing personality mid-session takes effect immediately.</div>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <div class="flow-num">3</div>
      <div class="flow-content">
        <div class="flow-step">PLANNING MODE</div>
        <div class="flow-desc">Appended only when planning mode is active. Restricts agent to read-only context gathering and forbids all modification tools.</div>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <div class="flow-num">4</div>
      <div class="flow-content">
        <div class="flow-step">MEMORY CONTEXT</div>
        <div class="flow-desc">Compressed GONDOLA.md tier-1 memories injected here — architecture notes, gotchas, patterns, user preferences from previous sessions.</div>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <div class="flow-num">5</div>
      <div class="flow-content">
        <div class="flow-step">RESURRECTION CONTEXT</div>
        <div class="flow-desc">State from the last interrupted session: what the agent was doing, which files it had read, what it was planning next. Enables seamless crash recovery.</div>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <div class="flow-num">6</div>
      <div class="flow-content">
        <div class="flow-step">STOPPING CRITERIA</div>
        <div class="flow-desc">When to call <code>done()</code>, what constitutes task completion, how to handle ambiguity without spinning.</div>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <div class="flow-num">7</div>
      <div class="flow-content">
        <div class="flow-step">MODEL-SPECIFIC GUIDANCE</div>
        <div class="flow-desc">13 model variants each receive tailored instructions. Kimi: 3-read max, surgical precision. GLM 5.1: long-horizon strategy, experiment loops. Qwen: exact placement, critical instruction following. Gemma: JSON tool format requirement, full content mandates.</div>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <div class="flow-num">8</div>
      <div class="flow-content">
        <div class="flow-step">PROJECT OVERVIEW</div>
        <div class="flow-desc">Compressed project index (~1000 tokens): file listing with symbol counts, key file summaries, detected dependencies. Cached between turns for performance.</div>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <div class="flow-num">9</div>
      <div class="flow-content">
        <div class="flow-step">TURN LIMIT WARNINGS</div>
        <div class="flow-desc">Urgency checkpoints injected at turns 10, 20, 30, 40, 45, 48 — escalating pressure to complete rather than continue exploring. At max, <code>force_done_at_max</code> triggers.</div>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <div class="flow-num">10</div>
      <div class="flow-content">
        <div class="flow-step">FILES ALREADY READ</div>
        <div class="flow-desc">Running list of files read this session. Prevents the agent from wasting tool calls re-reading content it already has in context.</div>
      </div>
    </li>
  </ol>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ PERSONAS ═══ -->
<section class="section" id="personas">
  <div class="section-label">12 — Identity</div>
  <h2 class="section-title"><span class="icon">🎭</span>Personas System</h2>

  <div class="info-box">
    Personalities are injected into the system prompt at runtime from a plain-text <code>.personality_config</code> file. No restart needed — changing personality takes effect on the next turn.
  </div>

  <div class="card-grid">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-accent-line" style="background: var(--magenta);"></div>
      <div class="card-title">.personality_config</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Freeform text file loaded by <code>load_personality()</code> in <code>system.py</code>. Injected directly between the base prompt and the stopping criteria. Persists across sessions.</div>
      <div class="card-meta"><span class="tag magenta">disk-persisted</span><span class="tag cyan">per-project</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-accent-line" style="background: var(--cyan);"></div>
      <div class="card-title">personalities.json</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Named preset library. Each preset is a slug → text mapping. Loaded from the gondola root. The Quick Macros "Persona" button in Daft UI surfaces these presets for one-click application.</div>
      <div class="card-meta"><span class="tag cyan">presets</span><span class="tag green">one-click</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-accent-line" style="background: var(--blue);"></div>
      <div class="card-title">API Endpoints</div>
      <div class="card-desc"><code>GET /api/personality</code> returns the current active personality text. <code>POST /api/personality</code> writes new text to disk. <code>GET/POST /api/personality-presets</code> manages the preset library.</div>
      <div class="card-meta"><span class="tag blue">REST</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ PLANNING ═══ -->
<section class="section" id="planning">
  <div class="section-label">13 — Execution Modes</div>
  <h2 class="section-title"><span class="icon">📐</span>Planning Mode</h2>

  <div class="info-box">
    Planning mode is a <strong>read-only execution mode</strong> that constrains the agent to context gathering and plan generation. No writes, no edits, no shell — the agent must call <code>done(plan)</code> with a proposed implementation.
  </div>

  <div class="card-grid">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-accent-line" style="background: var(--yellow);"></div>
      <div class="card-title">Activation</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Enabled via the Planning Mode checkbox in Daft UI. Sent as <code>planning_mode: true</code> in the request JSON. Passed to <code>build_system_prompt(planning_mode=True)</code> — no server restart needed.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-accent-line" style="background: var(--red);"></div>
      <div class="card-title">27 Blocked Tools</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Tool governance runs at execution time. Any modification tool returns <code>{"success": false, "error": "TOOL BLOCKED: You are in PLANNING MODE"}</code>. The error is fed back into the tool result stream so the model adapts.</div>
      <div class="card-meta">
        <span class="tag red">write_file</span><span class="tag red">edit_file</span><span class="tag red">delete_file</span><span class="tag red">run_command</span><span class="tag red">make_directory</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-accent-line" style="background: var(--green);"></div>
      <div class="card-title">Allowed Operations</div>
      <div class="card-desc">All read and analysis tools remain available: <code>list_files</code>, <code>read_file</code>, <code>search_file_content</code>, <code>map_project</code>, <code>get_skeleton</code>, <code>symbol_jump</code>, <code>smart_context</code>, <code>semantic_search</code>.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ PROVIDERS ═══ -->
<section class="section" id="providers">
  <div class="section-label">14 — API Layer</div>
  <h2 class="section-title"><span class="icon">🌐</span>Multi-Provider API Routing</h2>

  <div class="info-box">
    Each model in the registry declares a <code>"provider"</code> field. The API layer routes accordingly and applies provider-specific payload transformations before sending. Three providers are supported: <strong>Venice</strong>, <strong>Together AI</strong>, and <strong>Z.AI</strong>.
  </div>

  <div class="card-grid">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-accent-line" style="background: var(--cyan);"></div>
      <div class="card-title">Venice AI</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Default provider. Endpoint: <code>api.venice.ai/api/v1/chat/completions</code>. Adds <code>venice_parameters: {include_venice_system_prompt: true, web_search: true}</code> to every request. Balance headers <code>x-venice-balance-usd</code> / <code>x-venice-balance-vcu</code> extracted for cost tracking.</div>
      <div class="card-meta"><span class="tag cyan">web_search</span><span class="tag cyan">balance headers</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-accent-line" style="background: var(--green);"></div>
      <div class="card-title">Together AI</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Endpoint: <code>api.together.xyz/v1/chat/completions</code>. String <code>tool_choice</code> values are stripped (Together requires dict format). Vision requests truncate history to system + last 10 messages to avoid 500 errors. Serverless model discovery via <code>/v1/models</code>.</div>
      <div class="card-meta"><span class="tag green">serverless</span><span class="tag green">dict tool_choice</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-accent-line" style="background: var(--magenta);"></div>
      <div class="card-title">Z.AI (GLM)</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Endpoint: <code>api.z.ai/api/paas/v4/chat/completions</code>. Injects <code>thinking: {type: "enabled"}</code> and raises temperature to 0.6 for reasoning. Extended stream timeouts: 180s–600s depending on model.</div>
      <div class="card-meta"><span class="tag magenta">thinking mode</span><span class="tag magenta">temp 0.6</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-accent-line" style="background: var(--yellow);"></div>
      <div class="card-title">Vision Fallback</div>
      <div class="card-desc">When a non-vision model receives an image, Kimi K2.5 is invoked as a "Vision Helper" — it describes the image, and the description is injected into the conversation for the text-only model to use. Transparent to the user.</div>
      <div class="card-meta"><span class="tag yellow">auto-dispatch</span><span class="tag yellow">Kimi K2.5</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-accent-line" style="background: var(--blue);"></div>
      <div class="card-title">Dynamic Model Discovery</div>
      <div class="card-desc"><code>GET /api/provider-models?provider=together|venice</code> fetches live model lists, merges into the global <code>MODELS</code> dict, infers <code>native_function_calling</code> capability from model ID patterns, and persists additions to <code>custom_models.json</code>.</div>
      <div class="card-meta"><span class="tag blue">live discovery</span><span class="tag blue">custom_models.json</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-accent-line" style="background: var(--orange);"></div>
      <div class="card-title">Retry Logic</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Exponential backoff on transient API failures. Stream stall detection: if no chunk is received for <code>stream_timeout</code> seconds (model-specific), the connection is killed and an error event is emitted.</div>
      <div class="card-meta"><span class="tag orange">backoff</span><span class="tag orange">stall detection</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <br>
  <h3 style="font-size:14px;color:var(--cyan);font-family:Consolas,monospace;margin-bottom:14px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1px;">Model Capability Flags</h3>
  <table class="risk-table">
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Flag</th><th>Type</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><span class="risk-name">native_function_calling</span></td><td>bool</td><td>Supports OpenAI-style tool schemas</td></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="risk-name">supports_parallel_tools</span></td><td>bool</td><td>Can call multiple tools in one response turn</td></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="risk-name">preferred_tool_choice</span></td><td>str</td><td>"auto", "required", or None — sent with each request</td></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="risk-name">tool_choice_on_nudge</span></td><td>str</td><td>tool_choice override when model returns empty response</td></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="risk-name">needs_explicit_stop</span></td><td>bool</td><td>Model won't stop naturally — force termination after response</td></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="risk-name">force_done_at_max</span></td><td>bool</td><td>Inject done() tool call at turn limit instead of just warning</td></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="risk-name">native_vision</span></td><td>bool</td><td>Can process base64 image content natively</td></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="risk-name">stream_timeout</span></td><td>int</td><td>Seconds of silence before the stream is considered stalled</td></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="risk-name">max_agent_turns</span></td><td>int</td><td>Hard turn cap before forced completion</td></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="risk-name">context_limit</span></td><td>int</td><td>Max input tokens for context window management</td></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="risk-name">price_in / price_out</span></td><td>float</td><td>Per-million token pricing for cost accounting</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ STREAMING ═══ -->
<section class="section" id="streaming">
  <div class="section-label">15 — Real-Time Communication</div>
  <h2 class="section-title"><span class="icon">⚡</span>SSE Streaming</h2>

  <div class="info-box">
    <code>POST /api/chat</code> returns a Server-Sent Events stream via Flask's <code>stream_with_context</code>. A background thread runs the agent loop and pushes typed events into a thread-safe <code>queue.Queue</code>; the SSE generator yields them to the browser.
  </div>

  <h3 style="font-size:14px;color:var(--cyan);font-family:Consolas,monospace;margin-bottom:14px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1px;">Event Types</h3>
  <div class="card-grid">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title"><span class="tag cyan">status</span></div>
      <div class="card-desc">Progress messages: "Connecting to API", "Model thinking", "Executing tool…". Displayed in the UI header bar during processing.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title"><span class="tag green">text</span></div>
      <div class="card-desc">Streamed response chunks from the LLM, emitted as they arrive. Rendered progressively in the chat bubble.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title"><span class="tag magenta">thinking</span></div>
      <div class="card-desc">Separate reasoning block from Claude/GLM extended thinking. Displayed in a collapsible "thinking" section distinct from the final answer.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title"><span class="tag yellow">tool_calls</span></div>
      <div class="card-desc">Structured tool invocation data. UI renders a tool call bubble with the tool name and arguments before execution begins.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title"><span class="tag yellow">tool_done</span></div>
      <div class="card-desc">Tool execution result (success or error). Updates the tool bubble with the outcome. Error results are fed back into the conversation for the model to reason about.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title"><span class="tag orange">terminal</span></div>
      <div class="card-desc">Output from <code>UI.print()</code> calls inside tools — low-level progress lines rendered in the terminal drawer below the chat.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title"><span class="tag green">done</span></div>
      <div class="card-desc">Final event carrying session metadata: cost (USD/VCU), tokens in/out, turn count, duration, model ID, provider. Triggers UI stat panel update.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title"><span class="tag red">error</span></div>
      <div class="card-desc">Unrecoverable errors (API failure, timeout, stream stall). Terminates the stream and renders an error message in the chat.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <br>
  <div class="card-grid-2">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-accent-line" style="background: var(--red);"></div>
      <div class="card-title">Interrupt Support</div>
      <div class="card-desc">User can abort generation via <code>POST /api/interrupt</code>. Sets a global flag checked on each stream iteration. The loop breaks cleanly — all pending tool results are flushed before the <code>done</code> event is emitted.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-accent-line" style="background: var(--yellow);"></div>
      <div class="card-title">Stall Detection</div>
      <div class="card-desc">If no chunk arrives within <code>stream_timeout</code> seconds (model-specific, GLM 5.1 uses up to 600s), the stream is killed and an error event is emitted. Prevents silent hangs on provider outages.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ EXPRESSIONS ═══ -->
<section class="section" id="expressions">
  <div class="section-label">16 — Avatar System</div>
  <h2 class="section-title"><span class="icon">🧬</span>Avatar &amp; Expressions</h2>

  <div class="info-box">
    The Living Avatar is a state-aware sidebar character whose facial expression can be regenerated via AI image editing. Expressions are persisted to disk and the active avatar can be swapped at any time.
  </div>

  <div class="card-grid">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-accent-line" style="background: var(--cyan);"></div>
      <div class="card-title">Base Avatar</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Loaded from <code>/images/avatar.png</code> at the gondola root. Served via <code>/workspace-avatar</code>. Swapped via <code>POST /api/make-avatar</code> — accepts base64, copies to <code>.avatar.png</code> in the workspace.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-accent-line" style="background: var(--green);"></div>
      <div class="card-title">Expression Generation</div>
      <div class="card-desc">The <code>edit_image()</code> tool takes an expression prompt (e.g. "shocked", "grinning") and calls a Venice image-edit model. The prompt is forced to <em>"Change facial expression to X. Keep same person, style, character."</em> — preventing character drift.</div>
      <div class="card-meta"><span class="tag green">qwen-edit</span><span class="tag green">seedream-v4-edit</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-accent-line" style="background: var(--yellow);"></div>
      <div class="card-title">Expression Storage</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Saved to <code>/expressions/</code> at the gondola root as <code>expr_{sanitized_prompt}_{timestamp}.png</code>. Served via <code>/workspace-expressions/&lt;filename&gt;</code>. Not workspace-specific — shared across all projects.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-accent-line" style="background: var(--magenta);"></div>
      <div class="card-title">Edit Model Config</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Active edit model and style preset stored in <code>.edit_model</code> JSON. Managed via <code>GET/POST /api/edit-model</code>. Two options: <strong>qwen-edit</strong> (fast, lower quality) vs <strong>seedream-v4-edit</strong> (slow, better quality).</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-accent-line" style="background: var(--blue);"></div>
      <div class="card-title">Image Processing</div>
      <div class="card-desc">PIL auto-converts to RGB JPEG at 85% quality before sending to Venice. Images over 512px on the longest edge are resized. Reference image (base avatar) is base64-encoded and sent in the edit payload.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-accent-line" style="background: var(--orange);"></div>
      <div class="card-title">UI Integration</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Expression images rendered in chat as a gallery. Each image has a lightbox viewer with zoom/drag. A "Make Avatar" button promotes any expression to the active avatar instantly.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ DREAM CYCLE ═══ -->
<section class="section" id="dream">
  <div class="section-label">17 — Memory Consolidation</div>
  <h2 class="section-title"><span class="icon">💀</span>The Dream Cycle</h2>

  <div class="info-box">
    The Dream Cycle is a background consolidation process that runs at session startup when two conditions are met: <strong>24+ hours</strong> since last dream AND <strong>5+ sessions</strong> since last dream. State is tracked in <code>.gondola_memory/dream_state.json</code>.
  </div>

  <ol class="flow-list">
    <li>
      <div class="flow-num">1</div>
      <div class="flow-content">
        <div class="flow-step">DECAY</div>
        <div class="flow-desc">Applies exponential decay to memories based on age and type. Formula: <code>conf_new = floor + (conf_old − floor) × exp(−3 × days / decay_days)</code>. Architecture, Decision, Pattern, Gotcha, Preference: <strong>no decay</strong>. Progress: 7-day half-life. Context: 30-day half-life.</div>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <div class="flow-num">2</div>
      <div class="flow-content">
        <div class="flow-step">PRUNE</div>
        <div class="flow-desc">Memories that have decayed below a confidence threshold of <strong>0.3</strong> are removed. Daily memory files are atomically rewritten with a backup created first.</div>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <div class="flow-num">3</div>
      <div class="flow-content">
        <div class="flow-step">LLM CONSOLIDATION</div>
        <div class="flow-desc">Optional (requires client). All surviving memories are sent to the model for analysis. The model identifies contradictions, stale entries, and duplicates, then returns a JSON diff with <code>remove</code>, <code>merge</code>, and <code>update</code> operations. On conflict, the newer entry wins.</div>
      </div>
    </li>
  </ol>

  <br>

  <h3 style="font-size:14px;color:var(--cyan);font-family:Consolas,monospace;margin-bottom:14px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1px;">Memory Token Budgets (Tier 1)</h3>
  <table class="risk-table">
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Type</th><th>Budget</th><th>Decay</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><span class="risk-name">Architecture</span></td><td>375 tokens</td><td class="risk-score low">None</td></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="risk-name">Decision</span></td><td>375 tokens</td><td class="risk-score low">None</td></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="risk-name">Pattern</span></td><td>375 tokens</td><td class="risk-score low">None</td></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="risk-name">Gotcha</span></td><td>300 tokens</td><td class="risk-score low">None</td></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="risk-name">Progress</span></td><td>450 tokens</td><td class="risk-score medium">7-day half-life</td></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="risk-name">Context</span></td><td>450 tokens</td><td class="risk-score high">30-day half-life</td></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="risk-name">Preference</span></td><td>225 tokens</td><td class="risk-score low">None</td></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="risk-name" style="color:var(--text-dim)">TOTAL MAX</span></td><td><strong>2,250 tokens</strong></td><td>—</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ PROJECT INDEX ═══ -->
<section class="section" id="proj-index">
  <div class="section-label">18 — Codebase Indexing</div>
  <h2 class="section-title"><span class="icon">🗂️</span>Project Index</h2>

  <div class="info-box">
    Built at session startup and cached in <code>.gondola_index.json</code>. Scans the workspace up to 6 levels deep, extracts per-file symbols and summaries, and compresses the entire codebase to ~1000 tokens for the system prompt.
  </div>

  <div class="card-grid">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-accent-line" style="background: var(--cyan);"></div>
      <div class="card-title">Symbol Extraction</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Python: classes and functions with line numbers. JS/TS: exports and function declarations. Summary auto-generated from docstring, filename patterns (test_, config, utils, etc.), or symbol counts.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-accent-line" style="background: var(--green);"></div>
      <div class="card-title">Change Detection</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Each file entry stores a content hash. On the next session start, modified files are re-indexed while unchanged files are loaded from cache — keeping startup fast even on large codebases.</div>
