<!-- ── Analyst Mode ───────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section id="analyst">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="section-tag">Analyst Mode</span>
    <h2 class="section-title">Research drives thesis. Thesis drives trade.</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">
      Not a rules-based signal executor. A market analyst with a mandate to form its own thesis from first principles.
      Three phases per 45-minute cycle.
    </p>

    <div class="pull-quote">
      A thesis isn't "I think this goes up." It's a structured argument: what was found, why it moves prices, when it plays out, and what would prove it wrong. The agent will push back on wrong assumptions. It's here to make money, not to agree.
    </div>

    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr; gap: 1rem; margin-top: 1.5rem;">
      <div class="panel panel-blue">
        <div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:0.62rem;letter-spacing:0.14em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--blue-bright);margin-bottom:0.6rem;font-weight:600;">Phase 1 — Awareness</div>
        <ul style="list-style:none;font-size:0.83rem;color:var(--text);line-height:1.8;">
          <li><code>recall()</code> — reads prior thesis first</li>
          <li><code>get_world_news()</code> — 20+ RSS feeds</li>
          <li><code>fetch_url()</code> — full articles on significant stories</li>
          <li style="color:var(--text-dim);font-size:0.78rem;margin-top:0.4rem;">Two passes: Extraction then Synthesis</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="panel panel-blue">
        <div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:0.62rem;letter-spacing:0.14em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--blue-bright);margin-bottom:0.6rem;font-weight:600;">Phase 2 — Thesis</div>
        <div class="table-wrap" style="margin-top:0;">
          <table class="data-table" style="font-size:0.75rem;">
            <thead><tr><th>Confidence</th><th>Action</th></tr></thead>
