        <div class="tier-line"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="tier-body">
        <div class="tier-label">Tier 1 — Hot Context</div>
        <div class="tier-title">GALLEON.md</div>
        <div class="tier-desc">
          Always injected. The agent's current running knowledge — active theses, risk notes, market outlook.
          Built and maintained by the agent itself. Every cycle starts by reading this.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="memory-tier">
      <div class="tier-indicator">
        <div class="tier-dot tier-dot-2"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="tier-body">
        <div class="tier-label">Tier 2 — Daily Logs</div>
        <div class="tier-title">Mode-specific daily files</div>
        <div class="tier-desc">
          e.g. <code>analyst_2026-05-03.md</code>. Retrieved on demand by query.
          Each entry tagged with type, title, content, date, and confidence score.
          Switching strategies doesn't bleed memories — each mode writes to its own file.
        </div>
        <div class="type-pills">
          <span class="type-pill">thesis</span>
          <span class="type-pill">trade</span>
          <span class="type-pill">observation</span>
          <span class="type-pill">risk</span>
