      <strong style="color:var(--text-bright);">Confidence scoring:</strong>
      <span style="color:var(--text-dim);"> Every memory entry carries a score (0.0–1.0). The Dream Cycle decays low-confidence entries over time, keeping memory lean and high-signal.</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── Dream Cycle ────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section id="dream">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="section-tag">Dream Cycle</span>
    <h2 class="section-title">Offline memory consolidation.</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">
      Runs automatically between sessions — triggered at initialization if enough time has passed.
      Keeps memory lean and high-quality. Reversible if consolidation produces unwanted results.
    </p>

    <div class="dream-steps">
      <div class="dream-step">
        <div class="dream-step-icon">📉</div>
        <h4>Decay</h4>
        <p>Reduces confidence score on old entries proportional to age. Recent wins stay hot; stale calls fade.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="dream-step">
        <div class="dream-step-icon">✂️</div>
        <h4>Prune</h4>
        <p>Deletes entries with confidence below threshold (0.3). Dead theses don't take up context.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="dream-step">
        <div class="dream-step-icon">🧠</div>
        <h4>Consolidate</h4>
        <p>LLM pass rewrites and merges related memories, eliminates redundancy, promotes key insights.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="panel" style="margin-top:1rem;font-size:0.85rem;">
      Undo is available — consolidation backs up the pre-dream state before running. If the merge goes sideways, one command restores it.
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

