<section id="risk">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="section-tag">Risk Management</span>
    <h2 class="section-title">Enforced at the prompt level and in the tool.</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">All limits are injected into every cycle via <code>build_settings_suffix()</code> and hard-enforced inside <code>place_order()</code> before any API call hits Alpaca.</p>

    <div class="risk-grid">
      <div class="risk-card">
        <div class="risk-key">max_capital</div>
        <div class="risk-desc">Maximum total capital allocated to trading</div>
      </div>
      <div class="risk-card">
        <div class="risk-key">max_positions</div>
        <div class="risk-desc">Maximum number of open positions at once</div>
      </div>
      <div class="risk-card">
        <div class="risk-key">max_position_size</div>
        <div class="risk-desc">Maximum dollar size per individual position</div>
      </div>
      <div class="risk-card">
        <div class="risk-key">min_position_size</div>
        <div class="risk-desc">Minimum order size — avoids fractional noise</div>
      </div>
      <div class="risk-card">
        <div class="risk-key">stop_loss_pct</div>
        <div class="risk-desc">Stop-loss percentage applied across all positions</div>
      </div>
      <div class="risk-card">
        <div class="risk-key">min_stock_price</div>
        <div class="risk-desc">Filters out sub-penny and micro-cap junk</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="hold-callout">
      <strong>Hold List</strong> — tickers the agent <em>cannot sell under any circumstances</em>.
      Enforced in <code>place_order()</code> before the API call. A sell on a hold-listed ticker returns an error:
      <br><br>
      <code style="color:var(--red);background:rgba(248,81,73,0.08);border-color:rgba(248,81,73,0.2);">HOLD LIST BLOCK: TTWO is a designated hold.</code>
      <br><br>
      <span style="color:var(--text-dim);">Remove a ticker from the hold list to allow selling. The agent also tracks <code>daytrade_count</code> from account data and factors PDT rule into position decisions.</span>
